<title>CANADA: Hartmann - Last day forex rates unlikely euro value.</title>
<headline>Hartmann - Last day forex rates unlikely euro value.</headline>
<dateline>TORONTO 1997-05-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>Bundesbank directorate member Wendelin Hartmann said on Friday that he did not think that market foreign exchange rates on the final day before the launch of the euro single currency in 1999 would be used as final conversion rate for the new currency.</p>
<p>&quot;In my view, it is not very likely that the market rates on the very last day before the start of EMU will be taken as a basis (for conversion rates),&quot; Hartmann told a conference at the Forex 97 meeting in Toronto.</p>
<p>--Frankfurt Newsroom +49 69 756525</p>
